SLG LiveSite Portlet




Standard Life WrapWe believe our Wrap offers the fullest, most flexible, coherent, and stable adviser platform in the market and is consistently evolving to stand the test of time. Since the launch in 2006, we’ve helped businesses transform their service to clients and adapt to the changing regulatory landscape. We continue to grow and are committed to helping you build long term business success.
Standard Life won the Aberdeen Platform Awards in 2014 and 2015 and was voted Best Large Platform Provider (AUM over £12.5 billion) by the adviser community.Are you prepared?Keep up to date with the changes and trends happening across our industry, along with the challenges and opportunities they present. Visit our Smarter Business Hub on Money Marketing for commentary and debate from a range of industry experts.Money Marketing Smarter Business HubWe’re the first scale platform in the UK to move entirely to unbundled (clean) mutual fund share classes for both new and existing clients. This means we are ready to help you meet the requirements of the sunset clause which takes effect on 6 April 2016.Find out how the sunset clause affects you 
Business benefits


Access to discretionary investment managers on the platform
Improved business efficiency giving you more time to spend with your clients
Greater functionality with online tools for client management
Dedicated support services



Client benefits


Flexible investment choices supported by robust investment capability
Potential for better deals with discounted funds
Client access to view their portfolio online
Wide range of funds and tax wrappers
Transparent charging structure and clear client charges summary


We offer broad-based business support to help you prosper in the post RDR market. Our dedicated teams will help you get the most out of Wrap to grow your business whilst supporting you with your evolving day-to-day needs.Due diligenceStandard Life is committed to helping you conduct best practice due diligence that considers the needs of your clients and your business. View our 'how to' guide and read more about the key areas to consider.Due diligence on Wrap











